{"timestamp": "2026-07-16T14:54:48.416589+00:00", "level": "INFO", "logger": "llm_policy_library.orchestrator", "message": "query answered", "correlation_id": "ff328a73-4569-466b-8650-f3f7aa7d8f31", "query": "What policies relate to logging and monitoring?", "answer": "The supplied controls that relate to logging and monitoring are the following:\n\n- AU\u20112 (Event Logging) \u2014 defines what event types the system must be capable of logging, coordination with other organizational entities on logging needs, specifying which event types to log and their frequency or triggering situations, providing a rationale for adequacy for investigations, and periodic review/update of the selected event types [au-2].\n\n- AU\u201112 (Audit Record Generation) \u2014 requires audit record generation capability for the event types identified under AU\u20112a for specified system components, allows designated personnel/roles to select which event types are logged by specific components, and requires generated audit records to include the contents defined in AU\u20113 for the event types in AU\u20112c [au-12].\n\n- AU\u20116.4 (Central Review and Analysis) \u2014 requires capability to centrally review and analyze audit records from multiple system components, supporting consolidated monitoring and analysis [au-6.4].\n\n- AU\u20116.5 (Integrated Analysis of Audit Records) \u2014 requires integration of audit-record analysis with other data sources (e.g., vulnerability scanning, performance data, system monitoring, or other organization-defined sources) to improve detection of inappropriate or unusual activity [au-6.5].\n\n- MA\u20114.1 (Logging and Review \u2014 Maintenance) \u2014 requires logging of organization-defined audit events for nonlocal maintenance and diagnostic sessions and review of those maintenance/diagnostic audit records to detect anomalous behavior [ma-4.1].\n\nIf you need policy text or template language for any one of these controls (for example, an organizational policy statement implementing AU\u20112 or AU\u20116.4), indicate which control(s) and I will draft it using only the corresponding control content above.", "latency_ms": 8507.9, "document_count": 5, "citations": ["au-2", "au-12", "au-6.4", "au-6.5", "ma-4.1"], "is_fallback": false}
